description.narrative:
The Project is expected to:

-   generate around 607GWh of clean, zero emissions electricity per annum, serving approximately 125,000 individual households; 
-	avoid greenhouse gas emissions ("GHG") of approximately 390,000 tons of CO2 per annum 
-   diversify Jordan's fuel mix and improve energy security by generating electricity from a domestic resource;
-	help lower NEPCO's average generation costs (average of US12 cents/KWh in 2015) and contribute towards an improvement in NEPCO's financial position; and
-   help Jordan meet an increasing demand for electricity, in part driven by the growing influx of refugees in the country.
